{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":994,"text":"I was 10 years old when I learned\nwhat the word \"genocide\" meant."},{"time":6755,"text":"It was 2003,"},{"time":8483,"text":"and my people were being brutally\nattacked because of their race --"},{"time":12609,"text":"hundreds of thousands murdered,"},{"time":14437,"text":"millions displaced,"},{"time":16409,"text":"a nation torn apart at the hands\nof its own government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20199,"text":"My mother and father immediately began\nspeaking out against the crisis."},{"time":24413,"text":"I didn't really understand it,"},{"time":25923,"text":"except for the fact\nthat it was destroying my parents."},{"time":29391,"text":"One day, I walked in on my mother crying,"},{"time":33128,"text":"and I asked her why\nwe are burying so many people."},{"time":38400,"text":"I don't remember the words that she chose"},{"time":41127,"text":"to describe genocide to her\n10-year-old daughter,"},{"time":45388,"text":"but I remember the feeling."},{"time":47741,"text":"We felt completely alone,"},{"time":50820,"text":"as if no one could hear us,"},{"time":52762,"text":"as if we were essentially invisible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56359,"text":"This is when I wrote\nmy first poem about Darfur."},{"time":61144,"text":"I wrote poetry to convince people\nto hear and see us,"},{"time":66156,"text":"and that's how I learned\nthe thing that changed me."},{"time":69291,"text":"It's easy to be seen."},{"time":71111,"text":"I mean, look at me -- I'm a young\nAfrican woman with a scarf around my head,"},{"time":76245,"text":"an American accent on my tongue"},{"time":78432,"text":"and a story that makes even the most\nbrutal of Monday mornings seem inviting."},{"time":84031,"text":"But it's hard to convince people\nthat they deserve to be seen."},{"time":88741,"text":"I learned this in my high school\nclassroom one day,"},{"time":91176,"text":"when my teacher asked me\nto give a presentation about Darfur."},{"time":94075,"text":"I was setting up the projector\nwhen a classmate of mine said,"},{"time":97994,"text":"\"Why do you have to talk about this?"},{"time":100113,"text":"Can't you think about us\nand how it will make us feel?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":103187,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":105351,"text":"My 14-year-old self didn't know\nwhat to say to her,"},{"time":109439,"text":"or how to explain the pain\nthat I felt in that moment,"},{"time":113325,"text":"and in every moment that we were forced\nnot to talk about \"this.\""},{"time":117420,"text":"Her words took me back to the days\nand nights on the ground in Darfur,"},{"time":122288,"text":"where we were forced to remain silent;"},{"time":124766,"text":"where we didn't speak over morning tea"},{"time":126981,"text":"because the warplanes overhead\nwould swallow any and all noise;"},{"time":131458,"text":"back to the days when we were told"},{"time":133605,"text":"not only that we don't\ndeserve to be heard"},{"time":136418,"text":"but that we do not have a right to exist."},{"time":139963,"text":"And this is where the magic happened,"},{"time":142466,"text":"in that classroom when all the students\nstarted taking their seats"},{"time":145713,"text":"and I began to speak,"},{"time":147006,"text":"despite this renewed feeling\nthat I didn't deserve to be there,"},{"time":150769,"text":"that I didn't belong there"},{"time":152233,"text":"or have a right to break the silence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155110,"text":"As I talked,"},{"time":156818,"text":"and my classmates listened,"},{"time":159485,"text":"the fear ebbed away."},{"time":162022,"text":"My mind became calm,"},{"time":163623,"text":"and I felt safe."},{"time":166796,"text":"It was the sound of our grieving,"},{"time":169717,"text":"the feel of their arms around me,"},{"time":172464,"text":"the steady walls that held us together."},{"time":175926,"text":"It felt nothing like a vacuum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178801,"text":"I choose poetry because it's so visceral."},{"time":182821,"text":"When someone is standing in front of you,\nmind, body and soul,"},{"time":186155,"text":"saying \"Witness me,\""},{"time":187380,"text":"it's impossible not to become\nkeenly aware of your own humanity."},{"time":191593,"text":"This changed everything for me."},{"time":193417,"text":"It gave me courage."},{"time":195883,"text":"Every day I experience\nthe power of witness,"},{"time":198498,"text":"and because of that, I am whole."},{"time":200623,"text":"And so now I ask:"},{"time":202129,"text":"Will you witness me?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":205401,"text":"They hand me the microphone"},{"time":207459,"text":"as my shoulders sink\nunder the weight of this stress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212343,"text":"The woman says,"},{"time":214325,"text":"\"The one millionth refugee\njust left South Sudan."},{"time":216790,"text":"Can you comment?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":218271,"text":"I feel my feet rock back and forth\non the heels my mother bought,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":222315,"text":"begging the question:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":223517,"text":"Do we stay, or is it safer\nto choose flight?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":226826,"text":"My mind echoes the numbers:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":229741,"text":"one million gone,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":231428,"text":"two million displaced,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":233074,"text":"400,000 dead in Darfur."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235818,"text":"And this lump takes over my throat,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237548,"text":"as if each of those bodies\njust found a grave"}]},{"cues":[{"time":240194,"text":"right here in my esophagus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242593,"text":"Our once country,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":243768,"text":"all north and south and east and west,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":246022,"text":"so restless the Nile couldn't\nhold us together,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":248964,"text":"and you ask me to summarize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251354,"text":"They talk about the numbers\nas if this isn't still happening,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":254413,"text":"as if 500,000 didn't just die in Syria,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":257654,"text":"as if 3,000 aren't still making\ntheir final stand"}]},{"cues":[{"time":260572,"text":"at the bottom of the Mediterranean,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":263760,"text":"as if there aren't entire volumes\nfull of fact sheets about our genocides,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268523,"text":"and now they want me to write one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271254,"text":"Fact:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":273883,"text":"we never talked over breakfast,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":276169,"text":"because the warplanes\nwould swallow our voices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278908,"text":"Fact:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280510,"text":"my grandfather didn't want to leave home,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":282998,"text":"so he died in a war zone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285647,"text":"Fact:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287011,"text":"a burning bush without God is just a fire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290652,"text":"I measure the distance between what I know"}]},{"cues":[{"time":292862,"text":"and what is safe to say on a microphone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295136,"text":"Do I talk about sorrow? Displacement?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":298054,"text":"Do I mention the violence,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":299471,"text":"how it's never as simple\nas what you see on TV,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302175,"text":"how there are weeks' worth of fear\nbefore the camera is on?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":307654,"text":"Do I tell her about our bodies,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":310298,"text":"how they are 60 percent water,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311773,"text":"but we still burn like driftwood,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313714,"text":"making fuel of our sacrifice?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":315620,"text":"Do I tell her the men died first,\nmothers forced to watch the slaughter?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":319752,"text":"That they came for our children,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":321378,"text":"scattering them across the continent\nuntil our homes sank?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":324556,"text":"That even castles sink\nat the bite of the bomb?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":329773,"text":"Do I talk about the elderly,"},{"time":331664,"text":"our heroes,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":333323,"text":"too weak to run, too expensive to shoot,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335958,"text":"how they would march them,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337365,"text":"hands raised, rifles at their backs,"},{"time":339636,"text":"into the fire?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":340816,"text":"How their walking sticks\nkept the flames alive?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":343110,"text":"It feels too harsh for a bundle of wires\nand an audience to swallow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348318,"text":"Too relentless,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":349778,"text":"like the valley that filled\nwith the putrid smoke of our deaths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353661,"text":"Is it better in verse?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":356114,"text":"Can a stanza become a burial shroud?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":358839,"text":"Will it sting less if I say it softly?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":360694,"text":"If you don't see me cry,\nwill you listen better?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":363021,"text":"Will the pain leave\nwhen the microphone does?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":365161,"text":"Why does every word feel\nas if I'm saying my last?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":370256,"text":"Thirty seconds for the sound bite,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":372447,"text":"and now three minutes for the poem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375320,"text":"My tongue goes dry the same way we died,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":379408,"text":"becoming ash, having never been coal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384311,"text":"I feel my left leg go numb,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":386621,"text":"and I realize that I locked my knees,"},{"time":389502,"text":"bracing for impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391737,"text":"I never wear shoes I can't run in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396330,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397988,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404847,"text":"So, I wanted to leave on a positive note,"},{"time":409108,"text":"because that's the paradox\nthat this life has been:"},{"time":412608,"text":"in the places where I learned\nto cry the most,"},{"time":415632,"text":"I also learned how to smile after."},{"time":419615,"text":"So, here goes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424837,"text":"\"You Have a Big Imagination"},{"time":428325,"text":"or"},{"time":429626,"text":"400,000 Ways to Cry.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":434434,"text":"For Zeinab."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436784,"text":"I am a sad girl,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":439325,"text":"but my face makes other plans,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":442034,"text":"focusing energy on this smile,\nso as not to waste it on pain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446880,"text":"The first thing they took was my sleep,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":449427,"text":"eyes heavy but wide open,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":451769,"text":"thinking maybe I missed something,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453817,"text":"maybe the cavalry is still coming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456015,"text":"They didn't come,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":457284,"text":"so I bought bigger pillows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":461508,"text":"My grandmother could cure anything"}]},{"cues":[{"time":465236,"text":"by talking the life out of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467847,"text":"And she said that I could make\na thief in a silo laugh"},{"time":471136,"text":"in the middle of our raging war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473240,"text":"War makes a broken marriage bed\nout of sorrow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478198,"text":"You want nothing more than to disappear,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":480403,"text":"but your heart can't salvage\nenough remnants to leave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484848,"text":"But joy --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486216,"text":"joy is the armor we carried across\nthe borders of our broken homeland."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492687,"text":"A hasty mix of stories and faces"},{"time":496263,"text":"that lasts long after the flavor is gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500018,"text":"A muscle memory that overcomes\neven the most bitter of times,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":503952,"text":"my memory is spotted with\ndays of laughing until I cried,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":508525,"text":"or crying until I laughed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510184,"text":"Laughter and tears are both\ninvoluntary human reactions,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514177,"text":"testaments to our capacity for expression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517374,"text":"So allow me to express"}]},{"cues":[{"time":519231,"text":"that if I make you laugh,"},{"time":520945,"text":"it's usually on purpose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523048,"text":"And if I make you cry,"},{"time":524799,"text":"I'll still think you are beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527267,"text":"This is for my cousin Zeinab,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530696,"text":"bedridden on a random afternoon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534131,"text":"I hadn't seen her since the last time\nwe were in Sudan together,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":538181,"text":"and there I was at her hospital bedside"}]},{"cues":[{"time":542159,"text":"in a 400-year-old building in France."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547047,"text":"Zeinab wanted to hear poems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550179,"text":"Suddenly, English, Arabic\nand French were not enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554253,"text":"Every word I knew became empty noise,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":557664,"text":"and Zeinab said, \"Well, get on with it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":559962,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":561063,"text":"And I read her everything that I could,"},{"time":564249,"text":"and we laughed,"},{"time":565609,"text":"and we loved it,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":566789,"text":"and it was the most important stage\nthat I've ever stood on,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570788,"text":"surrounded by family,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":572623,"text":"by remnants of a people who were given\nas a dowry to a relentless war"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577423,"text":"but still managed\nto make pearls of this life;"}]},{"cues":[{"time":580903,"text":"by the ones who taught me\nto not only laugh,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":584643,"text":"but to live in the face of death;"}]},{"cues":[{"time":587537,"text":"who placed their hands across the sky,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":589967,"text":"measuring the distance to the sun\nand saying, \"Smile;"},{"time":593358,"text":"I'm gonna meet you there.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":595798,"text":"And for Zeinab --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598122,"text":"Zeinab, who taught me love\nin a place like France,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":602424,"text":"Zeinab, who wanted to he.ar\npoems on her deathbed --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":608471,"text":"Dilated fibromyalgia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611783,"text":"Her heart muscles expanded"},{"time":614938,"text":"until they couldn't function."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617190,"text":"And she held me,\nand she made me feel like gold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621087,"text":"And I said, \"Zeinab,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":623481,"text":"isn't it strange that your only problem"}]},{"cues":[{"time":627025,"text":"is that your heart was too big?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":632420,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633643,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}